WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.934 --> 00:00:03.870
NARRATOR: On the South Side
of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania,

00:00:03.870 --> 00:00:06.572
in a densely wooded area,

00:00:06.572 --> 00:00:11.511
a dark and deadly legacy
lurks amongst the trees.

00:00:11.511 --> 00:00:13.312
[ Growling ]

00:00:13.312 --> 00:00:18.251
Locals tell of spirits that
haunt the woods of Bethel Park.

00:00:18.251 --> 00:00:19.652
[ Screaming ]

00:00:19.652 --> 00:00:22.755
They were the tragic victims
of a series of drownings

00:00:22.755 --> 00:00:24.557
that plagued the area,

00:00:24.557 --> 00:00:29.095
and now their restless spirits
wander the darkness

00:00:29.095 --> 00:00:31.864
in search of the loved ones
they've left behind.

00:00:31.864 --> 00:00:35.234 line:0%
Welcome to Hundred Acres Manor,

00:00:35.234 --> 00:00:39.205 line:0%
built on top of the haunted
grounds of Bethel Park.

00:00:39.205 --> 00:00:41.874
[ Siren wailing ]

00:00:43.776 --> 00:00:46.245
[ Screaming ]

00:00:46.245 --> 00:00:48.147
[ Laughs evilly ]

00:00:48.147 --> 00:00:51.017
Hundred Acres Manor
is celebrating its 10th year

00:00:51.017 --> 00:00:55.955
of luring victims into the woods
and drowning them...

00:00:55.955 --> 00:00:57.223 align:start size:47% position:53%
Fresh meat!

00:00:57.223 --> 00:00:58.658
...in terror.

00:00:58.658 --> 00:01:01.794 line:0%
Hundred Acres Manor
is actually set dead-smack

00:01:01.794 --> 00:01:03.062
in the center of the woods.

00:01:03.062 --> 00:01:05.064
There is nothing around.

00:01:05.064 --> 00:01:07.266
It's truly an ominous sight
to see.

00:01:07.266 --> 00:01:10.036
The location
of Hundred Acres Manor

00:01:10.036 --> 00:01:11.904
has a deep and a dark history.

00:01:11.904 --> 00:01:14.140
Our building actually used to be
an old swimming pool

00:01:14.140 --> 00:01:15.908
that closed decades ago.

00:01:15.908 --> 00:01:18.111
Tales of drownings and violence
littered the property.

00:01:22.081 --> 00:01:25.218
A lot of our staff members do
believe it's actually haunted.

00:01:25.218 --> 00:01:28.821
I myself --
I'm a little bit of a skeptic.

00:01:28.821 --> 00:01:31.323
But I have seen
some weird things go on.

00:01:31.323 --> 00:01:34.126
I will say that.

00:01:34.126 --> 00:01:36.328
[ Cheering ]

00:01:36.328 --> 00:01:38.631
NARRATOR:
Entering the Manor is easy.

00:01:38.631 --> 00:01:41.967
It's getting out
that's the real killer.

00:01:41.967 --> 00:01:45.571
[ Deep voice ]
I smell fresh blood.

00:01:45.571 --> 00:01:47.307 align:start size:56% position:44%
Let's hold hands.

00:01:47.307 --> 00:01:49.275
NARRATOR: Once inside
this house of horrors,

00:01:49.275 --> 00:01:51.744
guests will be required

00:01:51.744 --> 00:01:54.347
to descend into the catacombs
of the Manor

00:01:54.347 --> 00:01:56.215
by way of an elevator...

00:01:56.215 --> 00:01:57.416 align:start size:47% position:53%
Here we go.

00:01:57.416 --> 00:01:59.185
...that isn't exactly
up to code.

00:01:59.185 --> 00:02:01.320
[ Bang ]

00:02:01.320 --> 00:02:03.423 align:start size:56% position:44%
[ Laughs evilly ]

00:02:04.524 --> 00:02:07.426
If you survive that death trap,

00:02:07.426 --> 00:02:10.096
then the real nightmare begins.

00:02:10.096 --> 00:02:11.363
You're forced down a path

00:02:11.363 --> 00:02:13.232
through the bowels
of the Manor...

00:02:13.232 --> 00:02:14.400
[ Growls ]

00:02:14.400 --> 00:02:16.569
...to mingle with the demented,

00:02:16.569 --> 00:02:18.404
the deranged...

00:02:18.404 --> 00:02:20.173 align:start size:53% position:47%
Get back here!

00:02:20.173 --> 00:02:21.708
...and the damned.

00:02:23.342 --> 00:02:24.844 align:start size:56% position:44%
Aah! Oh, my God!

00:02:24.844 --> 00:02:27.714
The thing that really drives our
haunt is definitely our actors.

00:02:27.714 --> 00:02:31.017
My character's name
is Alexander McWiggins.

00:02:31.017 --> 00:02:33.219
He snarls and he snorts.

00:02:33.219 --> 00:02:35.254
[ Snorting ]

00:02:36.389 --> 00:02:37.991
A lot of stuff like that.

00:02:39.258 --> 00:02:41.894
[ Screaming ]

00:02:41.894 --> 00:02:44.363
We currently have
40 core actors,

00:02:44.363 --> 00:02:48.534
and then we also have
a supporting staff of 150 actors

00:02:48.534 --> 00:02:51.370
that do our startle scares,
our pop-ups...

00:02:51.370 --> 00:02:52.605 align:start size:38% position:63%
Aah!

00:02:52.605 --> 00:02:53.840
...all those intense moments

00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:55.408
that really send you
screaming out the door.

00:02:58.377 --> 00:03:00.346 align:start size:38% position:63%
Aah!

00:03:00.346 --> 00:03:03.249
Awesome.
Oh, my gosh, it was so much fun.

00:03:03.249 --> 00:03:04.283 align:start size:44% position:56%
I did it!

00:03:04.283 --> 00:03:05.585 align:start size:50% position:50%
It was good.
I did good.

00:03:05.585 --> 00:03:06.919
Interesting thing --

00:03:06.919 --> 00:03:09.088
You can tell who really loves
someone and who doesn't.

00:03:09.088 --> 00:03:10.756
You see the guys
walking through,

00:03:10.756 --> 00:03:12.825
and they've got their
girlfriends in front of them,

00:03:12.825 --> 00:03:15.127
and you know, they're telling
them, "Oh, I'll protect you.

00:03:15.127 --> 00:03:17.130
I'm right here with you."

00:03:17.130 --> 00:03:18.998
In reality,
they're using them as shields.

00:03:18.998 --> 00:03:20.833 align:start size:75% position:25%
Aah!

00:03:20.833 --> 00:03:23.436
I will be scared no matter
how many times I go in there.

00:03:23.436 --> 00:03:25.338 size:81% position:41% line:85%
Nightmares tonight, right?

00:03:23.436 --> 00:03:25.338 align:start size:34% position:66%
Nightmares.

00:03:25.338 --> 00:03:27.440 size:78% position:61%
I'm not -- I'm --
You think I'm going home?

00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:29.275 size:72% position:64%
I'm gonna sit in my car
and camp out.

00:03:29.275 --> 00:03:31.377 align:start size:63% position:38%
No, I can't do this!

00:03:31.377 --> 00:03:34.314
NARRATOR: But behind
this macabre wonderland

00:03:34.314 --> 00:03:36.582
lies a hidden secret,

00:03:36.582 --> 00:03:38.985
a ray of light that cuts through
the darkness.

00:03:38.985 --> 00:03:41.254
What makes Hundred Acres Manor
different

00:03:41.254 --> 00:03:42.855
than most other haunts
in the country

00:03:42.855 --> 00:03:44.523
is that we're actually
a charity haunt.

00:03:44.523 --> 00:03:47.193
To date, we've donated
over a million dollars

00:03:47.193 --> 00:03:48.995
to two great
local Pittsburgh charities,

00:03:48.995 --> 00:03:50.530
the Homeless Children's
Education Fund

00:03:50.530 --> 00:03:51.864
and Animal Friends.

00:03:51.864 --> 00:03:55.234
NARRATOR: But don't let
all that goodwill fool you.

00:03:55.234 --> 00:03:57.336
Hundred Acres Manor's
top priority

00:03:57.336 --> 00:04:00.473
is to take you
to the edge of sanity

00:04:00.473 --> 00:04:03.476
and then throw you over
into the abyss.

00:04:03.476 --> 00:04:05.044
We're not going inside.

00:04:05.044 --> 00:04:07.313
She thought about going inside,
but she's too scared right now.

00:04:07.313 --> 00:04:10.149
We incorporate the industry's
most talented actors,

00:04:10.149 --> 00:04:12.385
detailed sets,

00:04:12.385 --> 00:04:15.054
over-the-top animatronics.

00:04:15.054 --> 00:04:16.555
[ Growling ]

00:04:16.555 --> 00:04:19.325
Creating an incredible
attraction

00:04:19.325 --> 00:04:22.394
can really bring in a lot
of people for one common goal,

00:04:22.394 --> 00:04:24.030
and that's the love
of Halloween,

00:04:24.030 --> 00:04:25.998
and it's kept us in business
for 10 years,

00:04:25.998 --> 00:04:28.467
and that's a huge accomplishment
and an honor.

00:04:28.467 --> 00:04:31.670
[ Moans ]

